---
import DonateButton from "../components/DonateButton.astro";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About - Tacoma Porchfest">
    <section
        class="flex items-center justify-center bg-pf-red bg-cover bg-center pt-16 pb-8 md:pt-20"
        style="background-image: url('/red-texture.webp');"
    >
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center text-center px-4 max-w-3xl">
            <h1 class="font-heading text-pf-brown text-4xl md:text-6xl uppercase">About</h1>
            <p
                class="mt-4 mb-8 font-body text-pf-brown text-base md:text-lg font-light leading-relaxed"
            >
                Tacoma Porchfest's mission is to build community, celebrate Tacoma's neighborhoods,
                and connect neighbors through a free, walkable, and accessible celebration of
                diverse live music performed on porches.
            </p>
            <DonateButton variant="inverted" />
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="bg-pf-yellow px-6 py-12 md:px-12 md:py-16">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
            <h1 class="font-heading text-pf-brown text-3xl md:text-5xl uppercase mb-8 md:mb-12">
                Five Years of Tacoma Porchfest
            </h1>
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 md:gap-12">
                <div class="md:w-2/3">
                    <h2
                        class="font-heading text-pf-brown text-lg md:text-2xl font-medium mb-6 leading-snug text-stroke-brown"
                    >
                        Porchfest is in its fifth year and has expanded to a 2-day festival spanning
                        two neighborhoods straddling 6th Ave in Central Tacoma and the North End
                    </h2>
                    <p class="font-body text-pf-brown text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
                        (UPDATE THIS) Porchfest has been growing steadily since its inaugural year
                        (2022), when Porchfest featured 50 bands on 35 porch stages. In its second
                        year (2023), the event doubled in size featuring nearly 100 bands on 55
                        stages, this year, (2024), the event doubled again to over 200 bands on 65
                        porch stages, with an estimated 8,000-10,000 attendees - and continued
                        growth is anticipated in 2025.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="md:w-1/3">
                    <img
                        src="/image-6.avif"
                        alt=""
                        class="rounded-sm object-cover aspect-3/4 w-full"
                    />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="bg-pf-yellow px-6 py-4 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
            <div class="flex flex-col-reverse md:flex-row gap-8 md:gap-12">
                <div class="md:w-1/3 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
                    <img
                        src="/image-4.avif"
                        alt=""
                        class="rounded-sm object-cover aspect-4/3 w-full"
                    />
                    <img
                        src="/image-5.avif"
                        alt=""
                        class="rounded-sm object-cover aspect-4/3 w-full"
                    />
                </div>
                <div class="md:w-2/3">
                    <h2
                        class="font-heading text-pf-brown text-lg md:text-2xl font-medium mb-4 leading-snug"
                    >
                        Music and outdoor festivals are great vehicles for community building
                    </h2>
                    <p class="font-body text-pf-brown text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed mb-8">
                        While the porch or front yard is a typically private space reserved for
                        morning coffee and cookouts with family and friends, placing performers on
                        porch "stages" within a walkable radius creates opportunities for meaningful
                        exchange, connection, and joy which are all building blocks to building
                        healthy and vibrant communities.
                    </p>
                    <h2
                        class="font-heading text-pf-brown text-lg md:text-2xl font-medium mb-4 leading-snug"
                    >
                        We aim to build lasting community connections in Tacoma
                    </h2>
                    <p class="font-body text-pf-brown text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
                        What makes Tacoma Porchfest unique is that, because the festival takes
                        places on porches, which are typically considered private property and
                        &ldquo;off-limits,&rdquo; it creates an atmosphere which is both intimate
                        and unusually inviting. Diverse groups of attendees are welcomed into
                        private yards to enjoy music and dance. Once there, conversations take place
                        and meaningful connections are made between people of various races,
                        ethnicities, sexual orientations, gender identities, economics, and
                        disabilities.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="bg-pf-yellow px-6 py-12 md:px-12 md:py-16">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 md:gap-12">
                <div class="md:w-1/2">
                    <h2 class="font-heading text-pf-brown text-3xl md:text-5xl mb-6 leading-tight">
                        This machine builds community.
                    </h2>
                    <p class="font-body text-pf-brown text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed mb-8">
                        Tacoma Porchfest is organized by community members in partnership with
                        Central Neighborhood Council, North End Neighborhood Council, and the Sixth
                        Ave Business District. It is made possible with funding from Tacoma Venues
                        &amp; Events and individual donations from festival attendees. Tacoma
                        Porchfest is a City of Tacoma Sponsored Event.
                    </p>
                    <div class="flex justify-center md:justify-start">
                        <DonateButton />
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="md:w-1/2 grid grid-cols-2 gap-6 items-center content-center">
                    <img
                        src="/city_of_tacoma.avif"
                        alt="City of Tacoma"
                        class="max-h-36 object-contain mx-auto"
                    />
                    <img
                        src="/tacoma_venues_and_events.avif"
                        alt="Tacoma Venues & Events"
                        class="max-h-28 object-contain mx-auto"
                    />
                    <img
                        src="/tacoma_creates.avif"
                        alt="Tacoma Creates"
                        class="max-h-28 object-contain mx-auto"
                    />
                    <img
                        src="/central_neighborhood_council.avif"
                        alt="Central Neighborhood Council"
                        class="max-h-28 object-contain mx-auto"
                    />
                    <img
                        src="/north_end_neighborhood_council.avif"
                        alt="North End Neighborhood Council"
                        class="max-h-28 object-contain mx-auto"
                    />
                    <img
                        src="/sixth_ave.avif"
                        alt="6th Ave Business District"
                        class="max-h-28 object-contain mx-auto bg-white rounded-sm p-2"
                    />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Base>
